WEBVTT

00:03.138 --> 00:05.000
Welcome to the Life Church Podcast.

00:06.442 --> 00:13.110
We are in Acts 2 4 to 2 community, a family on a mission to bring a life of Jesus to warranty.

00:13.130 --> 00:21.140
We hope you're ready to hear what God has to say to you today through His Word and by His Spirit.

00:21.160 --> 00:21.961
Amen, amen, amen.

00:22.001 --> 00:25.005
If you've got your Bibles, you can turn to Romans chapter 5.

00:25.045 --> 00:27.428
That's fine, that's where we are.

00:28.649 --> 00:32.434
And we're going to be reading that

00:32.866 --> 00:34.048
chapter together.

00:35.771 --> 00:41.582
But before we get there, imagine you accidentally crash into your neighbour's car.

00:42.524 --> 00:52.722
All right, you kind of reversing out, you're a bit kind of bleary-eyed in the morning, maybe the street lamps aren't working and maybe it's stupidly they'd parked across your drive the night before because that's what

00:52.930 --> 00:55.934
you would have had to do, wouldn't they, if you're going to smash into their car.

00:56.295 --> 01:05.348
But anyway, you smash into their car and you kind of like break it all up and you go and wake them up and you knock on the door and like, you genuinely, you're sorry.

01:05.509 --> 01:07.031
You know, I'm so sorry.

01:07.371 --> 01:09.274
I've completely smashed the car up.

01:09.715 --> 01:12.459
You know, it doesn't matter how sorry we are.

01:12.840 --> 01:17.266
The car will not magically repair itself with our sorry.

01:17.707 --> 01:22.514
All right, we can say sorry a hundred times and that car will not get fixed.

01:23.010 --> 01:27.036
because there is a cost with fixing that car.

01:27.496 --> 01:34.666
There is a debt now that we owe to our neighbor because we have smashed into their car.

01:35.407 --> 01:36.969
Somebody has to pay.

01:38.211 --> 01:49.907
And today when we look at Romans 5 together, we're gonna discover what happens to us as humans when sorry is not enough.

01:50.688 --> 01:52.210
Believe it or not,

01:52.418 --> 01:57.323
your sorry and my sorry to God is not enough.

01:58.024 --> 02:02.649
And so Romans chapter five verses one to 11, this is what it reads.

02:04.231 --> 02:18.646
Therefore, since we've been justified through faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have gained access by faith into grace in which we now stand.

02:19.407 --> 02:22.130
And we boast in the hope of the glory of God,

02:22.530 --> 02:30.320
Not only so, but we also glory in our sufferings because we know that suffering produces perseverance.

02:31.081 --> 02:34.385
Perseverance character and character hope.

02:35.206 --> 02:44.798
And hope does not put us to shame because God's love has been poured out into our hearts through the Holy Spirit who has been given to us.

02:45.679 --> 02:51.506
You see, at just the right time when we were still powerless, Christ died for the ungodly.

02:51.970 --> 03:00.163
Very rarely will anyone die for a righteous person, though for a good person someone might possibly dare to die.

03:01.064 --> 03:05.330
But God demonstrates his own love for us in this.

03:06.252 --> 03:10.779
While we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

03:12.141 --> 03:20.754
Now since we've been justified by his blood, how much more shall we be saved from God's wrath through him?

03:21.346 --> 03:34.740
For if while we were God's enemies, we will reconcile to Him through the death of His Son, how much more have Him been reconciled, shall we be saved through His life?

03:35.641 --> 03:47.474
Not only is this so, but we also boast in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have now received reconciliation.

03:48.962 --> 03:54.167
13 years ago, Lucas and I, we are planting life church.

03:54.187 --> 03:58.372
Money is scarce, and Lucas isn't working.

03:58.412 --> 04:01.435
He's had to give up his previous job.

04:01.555 --> 04:03.096
I had small children at home.

04:03.497 --> 04:05.159
So we did a bit of a role reversal.

04:05.179 --> 04:08.162
I was starting work as a teacher again.

04:08.242 --> 04:09.943
Lucas was looking after the children.

04:10.564 --> 04:16.370
One Saturday, we were sat in brew coffee shop at the Riverside retail park in Warrington.

04:17.026 --> 04:23.733
We were enjoying a sausage balm and that kind of, I mean, that's irrelevant really, but just to let you know, we were enjoying a sausage balm.

04:24.193 --> 04:24.974
I know it was brilliant.

04:25.434 --> 04:30.980
And as we were coming out, we noticed our car was not in the space where we left it.

04:31.540 --> 04:33.923
In fact, it was three spaces to the right.

04:34.383 --> 04:43.572
It kind of swiveled round a bit and we realized that somebody had plowed into the back of our car, knocking it down the car park.

04:44.533 --> 04:45.714
I was so cross.

04:46.210 --> 05:12.164
So cross because it looked like our car was a write-off and then as we made our way to kind of examine the damage We noticed this little slip of paper on the windscreen You know you can't and you kind of straight away my mind went Yeah, this is this is someone going ha ha someone thinks I'm writing you a lovely little note, and I'm not and but as we opened it There was a genuine apology.

05:12.644 --> 05:13.906
I'm so sorry

05:14.786 --> 05:16.267
We've smashed into your car.

05:16.708 --> 05:18.810
Here is our telephone number.

05:19.210 --> 05:24.075
Please call us and we will repay you and pay for the damages.

05:26.337 --> 05:27.939
Someone had to fix the car.

05:29.120 --> 05:30.782
The car had been damaged.

05:31.442 --> 05:37.148
The people said sorry, but they owed us for the damage to our car.

05:39.010 --> 05:43.474
And you know, the book of Romans, it reminds us and it tells us

05:44.194 --> 05:47.177
that it doesn't matter how sorry each of us are.

05:47.638 --> 05:55.146
Romans 3 says, all have sinned and all fall short of the glory of God.

05:55.907 --> 05:58.930
You see, sin has repercussions.

05:59.551 --> 06:04.897
It separates you and I from God and it creates a debt.

06:05.698 --> 06:08.040
There is a debt that has to be paid.

06:08.100 --> 06:13.426
There is a cost for our sin that has to be paid.

06:13.890 --> 06:18.559
And there is a one of us here in this room today that hasn't sinned.

06:18.860 --> 06:19.621
We all have.

06:20.082 --> 06:25.372
And in God's economy, there is a debt that you and I need to pay.

06:25.833 --> 06:29.881
And Romans 6 tells us and explains to us what that debt is.

06:30.743 --> 06:36.594
The wages of sin or the debt of sin is death.

06:37.730 --> 06:41.114
A penalty needs to be paid for your sin and my sin.

06:41.394 --> 06:47.061
And the Bible tells us that the punishment for that debt is death.

06:48.202 --> 06:49.123
That's justice.

06:49.784 --> 06:57.973
When someone does something wrong and they're convicted in a court of law, the judge serves the justice.

06:58.414 --> 07:01.197
The punishment fits the crime.

07:01.738 --> 07:05.682
And our God is a God of justice.

07:06.402 --> 07:14.311
But just like a coin has two sides, our God is also a God of love.

07:15.232 --> 07:19.817
He's a God of justice, and he is a God of love.

07:20.478 --> 07:21.979
And here is the tension.

07:23.060 --> 07:27.525
Justice says that the debt of sin has to be paid.

07:29.367 --> 07:35.474
But the God of love says the sinner must be saved.

07:35.842 --> 07:39.668
And so God, he doesn't ignore the penalty.

07:40.349 --> 07:55.031
In verse 8 of the passage I've read, says this, but God demonstrates his own love for us in this, that while we were sinners, Christ died for us.

07:55.913 --> 07:59.378
God, in that moment, on the cross,

07:59.522 --> 08:01.864
He absorbed our debt.

08:02.185 --> 08:04.407
He paid the penalty.

08:04.787 --> 08:09.972
Jesus took the punishment that you and I deserved on the cross.

08:10.433 --> 08:12.415
God couldn't just cancel the debt.

08:12.735 --> 08:16.419
He couldn't just wipe our sin under the rug.

08:16.699 --> 08:21.984
He couldn't just forgive us because justice had to be served.

08:22.365 --> 08:26.068
And He placed that justice upon Jesus.

08:26.469 --> 08:27.890
Jesus paid.

08:27.970 --> 08:37.282
Our punishment, he took the penalty in full and God poured his love out on you and me.

08:38.104 --> 08:41.969
You see, love took our place.

08:42.770 --> 08:44.072
Love took your place.

08:44.192 --> 08:46.154
Love took my place.

08:46.214 --> 08:48.618
I'll come back to it again.

08:48.678 --> 08:57.810
God demonstrated his own love that while we were sinners, Christ died

08:58.018 --> 08:58.439
for us.

08:59.620 --> 09:05.587
Notice that verse doesn't say, Christ died for us when we improved.

09:06.288 --> 09:09.312
Christ died for us when we cleaned ourselves up.

09:09.332 --> 09:12.796
Christ died for us when we started trying harder.

09:13.237 --> 09:16.400
Christ died for us when we apologized enough.

09:16.901 --> 09:27.634
It says while we were sinners, while we were actively sinning, whilst we were going against the things that God said, He

09:27.746 --> 09:29.328
died for us.

09:31.131 --> 09:37.040
Sometimes I watch a TV programme called Bondi Beach and I watch the lifeguards.

09:37.100 --> 09:44.330
They're looking with their eyes and they're looking down the beach and suddenly they spot someone drowning.

09:44.530 --> 09:46.754
They're in trouble in the water.

09:47.214 --> 09:48.156
And what do they do?

09:48.196 --> 09:50.659
They shout advice, don't they?

09:50.840 --> 09:51.340
That's it.

09:51.501 --> 09:53.864
One army friend said, doggy paddle faster.

09:54.405 --> 09:55.186
No, they don't.

09:55.810 --> 10:08.428
They grab their gear and with all they might they run as fast as they can to the shoreline and they dive in and they swim as hard as they can to rescue the person and pull them out.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.472
And that's what God did for you and for me.

10:11.853 --> 10:13.956
He demonstrated his love.

10:14.316 --> 10:18.422
He didn't shout advice to us, live this way, live that way.

10:18.522 --> 10:19.323
No God.

10:19.724 --> 10:21.426
He put on flesh.

10:21.602 --> 10:28.671
full of love for you and me, and he stepped into our mess in order to rescue us.

10:29.832 --> 10:43.649
Two Corinthians 5, 21 says this, God made him who knew no sin to be sin for us, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God.

10:44.750 --> 10:45.551
What does that mean?

10:45.611 --> 10:51.058
It means that when we place our faith in Jesus Christ,

10:51.266 --> 10:58.437
Our sin is transferred onto him because he has paid the debt.

10:58.457 --> 11:02.343
And his righteousness is credited to us.

11:04.026 --> 11:07.010
It's something called justification.

11:07.431 --> 11:09.695
We are justified.

11:10.155 --> 11:19.730
We swap our sin for his righteousness and we become justified just as if

11:19.938 --> 11:21.800
I'd never sinned.

11:22.161 --> 11:34.254
When God looks at you and I through our faith in Christ, He sees us clothed with a righteousness of His Son, just as if I'd never sinned.

11:34.775 --> 11:43.285
Not because we've earned it, but because Jesus paid for it, because love took our place.

11:45.708 --> 11:47.730
Romans 5 says this.

11:48.450 --> 11:55.799
While we were God's enemies, we were reconciled to him through the death of his son.

11:57.441 --> 12:01.826
We were enemies, yet God moved towards us.

12:03.288 --> 12:06.993
Think of this prodigal son in Luke chapter 15.

12:07.533 --> 12:09.636
You know, the younger son, we know the story.

12:09.696 --> 12:14.802
He demands his inheritance and essentially saying, Father, I wish you were dead.

12:15.170 --> 12:19.636
He goes off with it, and he squanders it, and he hits rock bottom.

12:20.317 --> 12:22.460
And so he decides to return, doesn't he?

12:22.500 --> 12:28.569
He expects humiliation, maybe even a servant's position at best.

12:29.850 --> 12:31.012
But the father runs.

12:32.474 --> 12:35.999
In that culture, it was undignified for a man to run.

12:37.741 --> 12:38.583
But love ran.

12:38.623 --> 12:40.605
He embraced him.

12:41.146 --> 12:42.829
He put a robe on his finger.

12:42.869 --> 12:43.890
He placed

12:44.034 --> 12:47.338
a ring on his finger, a robe on his body.

12:47.378 --> 12:59.474
He killed the fattened calf, the son expected justice, but what he received in that moment was reconciliation and love from the father.

13:00.816 --> 13:02.798
And this is the picture of Romans 5.

13:03.459 --> 13:05.462
We were far off.

13:05.482 --> 13:06.563
We were wasteful.

13:07.404 --> 13:11.730
While we were enemies, God came to us.

13:12.130 --> 13:19.277
Christ died in order to bring reconciliation to each of us, to make us family.

13:19.898 --> 13:21.199
And that's a gape love.

13:21.659 --> 13:22.740
It's not deserved.

13:22.760 --> 13:24.502
It makes no demands.

13:24.582 --> 13:26.224
It's not reciprocated.

13:26.644 --> 13:30.808
It is divine love, unconditional love.

13:31.729 --> 13:33.010
A debt had to be paid.

13:34.211 --> 13:40.978
Love took our place and we moved from God's enemies to His family.

13:42.146 --> 13:45.429
And that's wonderful what the Lord has done for each of us.

13:46.650 --> 13:48.973
But now this is where it becomes personal.

13:50.414 --> 14:08.531
If God loved you and me like that, if Christ died for us while we are sinners, if justice was served and love was poured out, then the gospel should change how we treat other people.

14:09.713 --> 14:11.154
You see, culture says,

14:12.258 --> 14:14.981
Be kind to those who are kind to you.

14:16.023 --> 14:18.866
Love those only when they deserve it.

14:19.667 --> 14:23.172
Forgive people, but only when they've earned it.

14:24.113 --> 14:30.621
But the good news of Jesus to all of us is this, while you are still sinners, I love you.

14:30.641 --> 14:36.168
While you are still enemies, I died for you.

14:36.228 --> 14:40.594
And the wonderful news is that the Bible tells us

14:40.994 --> 14:43.097
exactly what to do with that.

14:43.918 --> 14:54.070
Ephesians 4 says be kind and compassionate to one another, forgiving each other just as in Christ, God forgave you.

14:55.572 --> 15:02.100
Colossians 3 says these words, forgive as the Lord forgave you.

15:04.022 --> 15:10.130
That means that just like God moved towards us,

15:11.362 --> 15:18.510
There will be times when we have to move towards people in our life who do not deserve it.

15:19.351 --> 15:24.177
You see, forgiveness, it always costs something.

15:25.939 --> 15:39.314
When someone hurts you and you choose to forgive them, you absorb the cost, your pride, your right to react retaliation,

15:40.066 --> 15:48.755
In a small way, every act of forgiveness mirrors the cross and what Jesus did for us.

15:50.677 --> 15:53.661
We don't forgive because they deserve it.

15:55.262 --> 15:58.226
We don't forgive because they've said sorry enough.

15:59.327 --> 16:04.512
We forgive because we know what it is to be forgiven ourselves.

16:06.134 --> 16:07.556
But let's be real for a moment.

16:08.657 --> 16:09.618
Sometimes.

16:11.010 --> 16:12.512
It's just too hard to forgive.

16:14.536 --> 16:16.539
Sometimes the pain is too great.

16:17.660 --> 16:21.126
Sometimes someone has wronged us in such a way.

16:22.408 --> 16:26.595
And we feel like I could never forgive that person.

16:28.558 --> 16:31.482
But Romans chapter five helps us again with that.

16:31.823 --> 16:38.994
In verse five it says, God's love has been poured out into our hearts

16:39.330 --> 16:41.653
through the Holy Spirit.

16:42.715 --> 16:52.029
The same love that sent Jesus to the cross now lives in you and me by His Spirit.

16:52.710 --> 17:02.204
God gives you His love to help you to forgive that person where it's too hard to forgive them.

17:03.165 --> 17:09.234
So when we feel that it might be impossible to forgive, God

17:09.794 --> 17:18.125
has given you a grace and a love to help you forgive someone who has wronged you.

17:20.027 --> 17:30.281
Do you remember my story about the car when I talked about how I was so cross, these people, they'd almost written off like the whole of the back of the car was kind of punched in.

17:31.222 --> 17:37.490
Well, a couple of months had passed by and still our car hadn't been fixed and

17:37.794 --> 17:43.282
And I was kind of getting a little bit irate now because I thought, this is out of order, through no fault of our own.

17:44.383 --> 17:49.130
Our car, we can't use it, it's messed up and these people promised us the money.

17:50.011 --> 18:00.186
And then one day, Lucas said to me, he said, Sarah, he said, I feel we need to free these people from their debt.

18:00.646 --> 18:06.194
We need to free them from paying for our car and we need to let them know.

18:06.434 --> 18:11.859
And we'd been in text with them, so we said, OK. We said, let's do it.

18:12.140 --> 18:14.342
And so we texted and said, we'd like to come and see you.

18:14.702 --> 18:22.129
And on the way, I remember driving up the Nutsford Road, and there was a co-op, and Luke slept, as he does.

18:22.930 --> 18:24.332
He has to go one step further.

18:24.512 --> 18:26.934
Let's buy them flowers and chocolate as well.

18:27.435 --> 18:30.378
And everything within me was just like seriously.

18:30.998 --> 18:34.962
Like, we're going to be a few thousand out of pocket here.

18:35.106 --> 18:36.788
and we're letting these guys get off.

18:37.708 --> 18:47.798
You know, later, we sat in the room with these people and we just began just to share with them the love of Jesus.

18:49.359 --> 18:51.522
We began to say things like, you know what?

18:51.902 --> 18:56.406
We're Christians and we're just going to free you from this debt.

18:56.426 --> 19:04.754
And there was this forgiveness that just came over me, this love of God that just enabled me just to see them as God saw them.

19:05.154 --> 19:10.682
and just to release them from that debt of paying for our car.

19:11.924 --> 19:21.819
You know, when God's love has been poured into our hearts, He helps us through the power of His Holy Spirit to forgive people.

19:22.680 --> 19:31.794
And what is impossible naturally becomes possible spiritually because God is living inside each of us.

19:33.826 --> 19:39.015
Finally today, the cross, it reveals the heart of God.

19:40.137 --> 19:46.249
God demonstrated his love for us in this while we were sinners.

19:47.070 --> 19:50.456
Christ died for us.

19:52.840 --> 19:58.130
There's the gospel in four words, Christ died for us.

19:58.722 --> 20:04.552
Those four words are historically true and personally life-changing.

20:05.254 --> 20:06.135
Christ died.

20:06.195 --> 20:18.277
There are so many history books outside of the Word of God written, declaring that a man called Jesus, who was crucified on a cross.

20:18.978 --> 20:21.202
So we know that took place.

20:21.730 --> 20:31.940
But we also know that that very historical account has brought transformation to our lives because a debt was paid.

20:32.561 --> 20:34.042
Justice was served.

20:34.542 --> 20:36.244
Love was demonstrated.

20:36.304 --> 20:45.093
The possibility of enemies becoming children of God and peace with God became possible.

20:46.154 --> 20:50.578
Romans 5 says, since we have been justified through faith,

20:51.106 --> 20:56.314
we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ.

20:57.095 --> 21:12.780
Not hopeful optimism, not one day just hoping there might be a heaven that we go to, but settled once and for all peace, knowing that we are forgiven, knowing that there is an eternity that we are going to spend with our Father.

21:15.223 --> 21:19.570
Today in this room, you might feel that you're not good enough for God.

21:20.322 --> 21:23.507
And if you feel that, listen, you are absolutely right.

21:24.528 --> 21:27.432
Not one of us here in this room is good enough.

21:28.253 --> 21:32.700
Not one of us is good enough for God, but Jesus is.

21:33.601 --> 21:39.750
He is someone who knew no sin and he has paid the bill of sin.

21:39.810 --> 21:41.132
He has paid that penalty.

21:41.432 --> 21:42.834
He has covered

21:42.978 --> 21:44.139
The cost.

21:44.159 --> 21:46.582
Imagine you're at a restaurant Valentine's night.

21:46.622 --> 21:48.664
Yeah, those of you went to a restaurant last night.

21:48.724 --> 21:50.025
Loads of you I can tell.

21:50.565 --> 21:50.906
All right.

21:51.046 --> 21:54.509
And you're sat there and said, ah, forgot my wallet, forgot my phone.

21:54.809 --> 21:55.230
Oh no.

21:55.250 --> 21:56.972
And then there's Chris Senior.

21:57.012 --> 21:59.254
He's happens to be sat on the table next to you.

21:59.274 --> 22:00.235
And he goes, it's all right.

22:00.675 --> 22:01.776
I'm as rich as anything.

22:01.796 --> 22:02.957
I'm a secret millionaire.

22:03.458 --> 22:06.080
I've paid the cost for you.

22:06.120 --> 22:06.741
Okay.

22:07.442 --> 22:09.244
And that is the story of the cross.

22:10.084 --> 22:11.826
Our debt has been paid.

22:12.162 --> 22:17.328
The sin, it of the penalty has been paid, the cost has gone.

22:18.008 --> 22:22.353
The bands are gonna come up now, but let me talk to you finally these few things.

22:25.477 --> 22:35.828
Once and for all, our debt has been paid, the cost has been covered, but are you still carrying the debt of sin?

22:36.729 --> 22:37.911
Are you still carrying it?

22:39.072 --> 22:41.074
Are you still holding onto it?

22:42.306 --> 22:46.251
And tonight I would say to you, listen, you do not need to hold on to your sin.

22:46.631 --> 22:58.725
You do not need to carry the weight of your sin because God has given you a way to swap your sin for his righteousness.

22:59.406 --> 23:02.610
You can give your sin to him tonight.

23:03.030 --> 23:09.938
You can say, Father, forgive me for the wrong I have done and in replacement

23:10.210 --> 23:14.517
you will receive the righteousness of his Son upon you.

23:15.038 --> 23:25.314
And in that moment, immediately in that moment, God looks at you just as if I'd never sinned, justified.

23:25.374 --> 23:30.522
You are made justified through your faith in Christ.

23:32.345 --> 23:38.034
The second thing I want to talk to about tonight is this, are you holding on to unforgiveness?

23:39.170 --> 23:47.161
Is there someone who needs to see the demonstration of God's love through you to them?

23:47.221 --> 23:52.228
Do you need to demonstrate God's love?

23:52.889 --> 24:06.186
And do you need to let go of what that person has done to you and through the power of the cross, through the strength of the Holy Spirit, through the love that God has poured on you?

24:06.206 --> 24:08.850
Do you need to forgive

24:08.962 --> 24:16.971
that person today, not because they deserve it, but because you didn't either.

24:18.653 --> 24:23.198
While we were sinners, Christ died for us.

24:25.961 --> 24:30.726
And as we sing this song now, two responses.

24:32.608 --> 24:33.950
Jesus, forgive me.

24:33.970 --> 24:37.714
Thank you for paying my debt of sin.

24:38.722 --> 24:40.204
I give it to you tonight.

24:47.474 --> 24:52.821
Give me the righteousness of your son, as I put my trust in you.

24:54.724 --> 24:59.430
Second thing, Lord, help me to forgive in this situation.

25:05.138 --> 25:06.520
Lord, I don't feel like it.

25:06.540 --> 25:08.242
They might not even deserve it.

25:10.754 --> 25:12.416
But you have forgiven me much.

25:12.456 --> 25:16.662
Help me to reflect you in this situation.

25:16.702 --> 25:20.247
Help me to demonstrate your love, God.

25:27.136 --> 25:35.848
At the cross, justice met love and love fulfilled justice.

25:38.131 --> 25:40.594
Jesus, we thank you.

25:41.378 --> 25:43.640
Thank you for your death on the cross.

25:45.262 --> 25:51.289
Thank you because your death provided a way for us to be justified.

25:53.231 --> 26:00.178
We couldn't pay the penalty for our sin, but you took it and you paid the cost.

26:04.343 --> 26:06.084
Thank you that we can stand.

26:08.767 --> 26:11.250
We can stand in your presence, God,

26:13.186 --> 26:32.283
can stand because of the righteousness of Jesus and help us to be those men and women who demonstrate your love to a world who needs to see your love.

26:32.303 --> 26:33.805
We've come to the end of this week's message.

26:34.427 --> 26:36.210
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

26:36.834 --> 26:43.698
Please keep up to date with everything that's happening by visiting our website at www.5churchbarrington.com

